# #905 same-class extension: classify the mouse echo port (TCP 7) into
# iperf-b so mouse and elephant traffic share the same 10 Gb/s shaper
# queue. Used when MOUSE_CLASS=iperf-b is set on the orchestrator.
#
# Term number 4 sits AFTER the four base terms (0..3) in
# cos-iperf-config.set. Order matters in stateful filter evaluation —
# we want the explicit port-7 match to win over the default
# fallthrough to best-effort.
#
# IPv4 only for now (the test target is 172.16.80.200). v6 mirror
# would be a follow-up if the harness adds 2001:559:8585:80::200.

set firewall family inet filter bandwidth-output term 4 from destination-port 7
set firewall family inet filter bandwidth-output term 4 then forwarding-class iperf-b
set firewall family inet filter bandwidth-output term 4 then count iperf-b-mice
set firewall family inet filter bandwidth-output term 4 then accept
